  "text": "The need for cooperativity with other oncogenic hits is entirely expected for an authentic human oncogene (7), which was the reason why we analyzed the amplification of c-myc and EGFR in the same cohort of samples. c-myc gene was amplified in 26.5% of analyzed samples, slightly above reported frequencies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , but did not show any co-ordination with CCND1 amplification. Barnes and Gillette (23) have also shown that CCND1 gene is amplified in cases were c-myc is not. Although this reciprocal amplification seems to be consistent with the observation that c-myc represses the transcription of cyclin D1 (24), direct evidence is still lacking for a reciprocal relationship between the expression of c-myc and that of cyclin D1.",
